title: For Sale:  Winchester Pre-64 Model 94 30-30 and 3 boxes of Hornady LeveRevolution ammo
postcontent:
For sale is a beautiful Winchester Pre-64 Model 94 lever action rifle in 30-30 Winchester caliber.  If you look at the successful bids on Gunbroker.com, a rifle in this nice of condition would sell for $700, plus.

I prefer to sell to someone in Washington State so here's the deal.  If you live in Washington State, I will sell it for $600 (firm) and drive part way to meet you at a gun shop to do a face to face sale and transfer paperwork.  In other words, if you live on the west side I would meet you in Ellensburg.  If you live in Spokane, I would meet you in Ritzville.  If you live in the Tri-Cities or you drive to Kennewick to meet me, I will knock $50 off.

Included are three boxes of Hornady LeveRevolution 30-30 ammo.  At least a 75.00 value and it is almost impossible to find right now. 

The Serial No. is 223XXXX, which means it was manufactured in 1956.  It is one of the nicest original Pre-64 Model 94’s that you will ever find and it functions perfectly.  It is rust free and has nearly 100% of the original bluing.  It does not have any touch-up bluing- it is all original.  The stock, which has never been sanded or refinished, has only some faint scratches and dents.  All I have ever done to the stock is wipe on a little oil finish, as they can dry out over time.  The attached photos show the actual rifle for sale and were taken on February 19, 2015.

The rifle has a Redfield peep sight and sling swivels.  In addition, I installed a new follower for the Hornady LeveRevolution bullets.  The original follower is included. 

I am not interested in any trades.  Sorry!

The background check that is now required in Washington by Initiative 594 and subsequent transfer of the gun to the buyer can be performed at any gun shop.  If you pick it up in Kennewick, I prefer the Hole in the Wall gun shop on Deschutes.  The fee is $25.00, payable by the buyer.  I checked and there is no sales tax on the private sale, even though the transfer occurs at a gun store.

Anyway, give me a call at the number listed below if you have any questions or would like to see the rifle and purchase it.  I have 20 high resolution photos that I can email if you are interested.

Thanks for looking!

REDACTED

title: Want To Buy:  German Mauser K98k, (even sporterized), Cheap SKS
postcontent:
I want a German K98k. It doesn't have to be some super-awesome collector that  some master German sniper used to halt a red army advance while he single-handedly took out a tank or something crazy like that. I'd mainly like one that hasn't been screwed with (Sporterized) in any permanent way. If someone put it into some sporter stock or whatever, I'm  interested if the bore is really good, and the rifle is otherwise in good shape (As I'll just buy a K98k stock, and try to "Un-bubba" it.

But, I will insist on a German Mauser. I have a VZ24, and while it's nice, It just doesn't quite scratch that itch, nor will a Yugo M24/48.

I'd also like an SKS. Nothing fancy, actually cheaper is better, especially if it's one that doesn't have some real military significance. If it's a Norinco made for civilians that's beat up that's fine. I'd like a project, but I don't like refinishing milsurp. 

I don't have much to trade, though I do have a few assorted rounds, some 12GA slugs, a few 300 Winchester Mag rounds, some.22LR, as well as two AR vertical grips, and an LED pistol light. Naturally I'd include cash, but I have some stuff I don't need, and I'd rather give it to someone who could use it, and work out a deal so they get some stuff they could use, and I save some cash. Saves me the trouble of selling some of this stuff.

Of course all laws must be obeyed, NJ FID card, and all that other happy horse-crap this stupid state makes us do.

title: For Sale/Trade:   on a serious note
postcontent:
Ok listen people.  Enough of all the over priced ammo.  Stop with the constant patterns of trying to screw each other over.
 Even with the guns i see it daily. 
What happened to all the guys who use to make this fun and make deals and actually stick to the deal and keep their word like a man? 
 Now all we see is people wanting more more more.  Nobody is happy with just making a good honest trade or sell.  The only way a deal is made is if each person is making a huge ass profit which is impossible. 
 Ive seen it myself many times lately trying to make a deal.  Someone will have a gun listed for trade but not mention what they would trade for that way they can keep it like a auction.  I offer many guns worth the same value and all i ever get is 'no thanks' .  Has nothing to do with what the gun is it has to do with the fact they look up value on some stupid website and the value is to close to what they have so therefore they cant make a profit and say no thanks.  
 Your not ALWAYS going to come out on top if thats all you seem to care about. 
 Try making trades for guns that you may enjoy shooting and youd probably trade a lot faster instead of everyone using this to rip each other off.
  The cash value is 200 trade value is 700 crap is really stupid also.  Trading makes it worth more?????? How?  If i have the same gun youd say im overpriced  but when you have it its worth its weight in gold? 
 I have met several really nice honest guys on here but the majority of you are nothing more than smartass kids who spend to much time blogging about guns instead of actually shooting the guns.  
 90% of all guns for sale used i can buy new cheaper all day. 
 Chill out people and come back down to earth. 
 And by the way all you ammo gougers are causing us to be limited again on how many boxes we can buy now so thanks for screwing us worse than the gov does.
